## User Flow

### Creating a Document

1. Click "New Document" button ‚Üí Opens DocumentUIManager creation modal
2. OR click "Use Template" ‚Üí Opens template selection ‚Üí Pre-fills creation modal
3. Fill in details (category, type, tags, content, approval workflow)
4. Submit ‚Üí Document created ‚Üí View refreshes

### Viewing/Editing Documents

1. Click document card ‚Üí Opens viewer modal
2. OR click options (‚ãØ) ‚Üí Select "View" from menu
3. In viewer, click "Edit" ‚Üí Opens edit modal
4. Make changes ‚Üí Submit ‚Üí Document updated ‚Üí View refreshes

### Sharing Documents

1. Click options (‚ãØ) ‚Üí Select "Share"
2. OR open viewer ‚Üí Click "Share"
3. Choose sharing method:
   - Copy link
   - Email specific users
   - Add collaborators

### Deleting Documents

1. Click options (‚ãØ) ‚Üí Select "Delete"
2. Confirm deletion in modal
3. Document removed ‚Üí View refreshes ‚Üí Success notification

## Technical Notes

### Data Flow

1. `DocumentManager` - Handles CRUD operations and data persistence
2. `DocumentUIManager` - Provides enhanced modal interfaces
3. `app.js` - Coordinates view rendering and user interactions
4. `ModalComponent` - Displays all modals (form, custom, confirm, menu)

### Event Handling

- Tab clicks: `onclick="studyHallApp.filterDocumentsByCategory('category')"`
- Card clicks: `onclick="studyHallApp.viewSimpleDocument(id)"`
- Options: `onclick="event.stopPropagation(); studyHallApp.showDocumentOptions(id, event)"`
- Search: Event listener on input element

### Styling

- Inline styles used for quick prototyping
- Hover effects applied via onmouseover/onmouseout
- Grid layout controlled by CSS
- Responsive design maintained

